originalText.text: My 5 year old grandson, just entering kindergarten this month was visiting me in NY for two weeks.  I registered him for lego-robotics in a morning session.  He loved it, begged for me to enroll him for the second week, which I did.  He wants to go next summer for full day.  I was sooo impressed with the teachers, the general friendly and fun atmosphere, the quality of the teaching, and the intelligence  with which the teachers handled these young energetic kids.

originalText.text: My 11-year-old daughter had an amazing experience. She created a landscape and multi-level residence with light switches and various kinds of rooms on minecraft. She also learned how to code and designed her own racing game in one week! She was so excited every day to talk about what she had done and had a great time playing/winning against her family in her own game at the end of the week.

originalText.text: So absurdly overpriced that it's hard to believe. My son had fun, true, but we paid the same price for a half day here versus nearly the same cost for a full day with transportation at Storefront Science, where he had an incredible time. Despite the exorbitant tuition, they still have the audacity to not provide snack. Who doesn't provide snack?? And don't even get me started on the communication issues... One day's notice for start of session info and same thing notifying us about the kids' presentations on the last day. Speaking of the presentations, they're 15 minutes after drop off and they kind of expect you to take your kid home after the presentation even though you've paid for a full day. It's just ridiculous. We won't be at Robofun again.
